nella "Commedia"}{\plain \fs24 \f2   (Florence: Olschki, 1983), pp. 63, 71-73.  In this formulation Virgil is to \softline
Beatrice as John was to Christ.  For an earlier moment in Dante's writing that is based on exactly \softline
such a typological construction, one in which Guido Cavalcanti's Giovanna/John the Baptist is \softline
